<collectingCountry box="[840,984,615,641]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Deeming, J. C. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M." box="[1025,1360,615,642]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref28013" refString="Deeming, J. C. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M. (2012) Chloropidae from the Arabian Peninsula (Diptera: Cyclorrhapha). Zoology in the Middle East. 58, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="2012">Deeming &amp; Al-Dhafer (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[331,421,651,677]" name="Lesotho" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Lesotho</collectingCountry>
and further recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[737,835,651,677]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[848,985,651,677]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1094,651,677]" name="Namibia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Namibia</collectingCountry>
and “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1163,1273,651,677]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Rhodesia</collectingCountry>
” (
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1386,651,677]" name="Zambia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,276,687,714]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
